doc.ContractDescription: WE PROPOSE TO PERFORM A CENSUS OF CIRCUMSTELLAR DISKS IN THE NEAREST STAR-FORMING REGIONS AND YOUNG ASSOCIATIONS (150 PC, 0.1-15 MYR) USING DATA FROM THE WIDE-FIELD INFRARED SURVEY EXPLORER (WISE). IN THIS CENSUS, WE WILL 1) COMPILE WISE PHOTOMETRY FOR ALL KNOWN KNOWN MEMBERS OF OUR TARGET POPULATIONS, 2) CLASSIFY THE SPECTRAL ENERGY DISTRIBUTIONS OF THE KNOWN MEMBERS, 3) SEARCH FOR NEW MEMBERS OF THESE REGIONS BASED ON WISE COLORS THAT ARE INDICATIVE OF DISKS, AND 4) MEASURE DISK FRACTIONS AT 5-15 MYR THAT ARE MORE STATISTICALLY SIGNIFICANT THAT THOSE PREVIOUSLY AVAILABLE, PARTICULARLY AMONG LOW-MASS STARS AND BROWN DWARFS, WHICH WILL IMPROVE ESTIMATES OF DISK LIFETIMES. THIS PROPOSED WORK IS RELEVANT TO NASA'S OBJECTIVES OF UNDERSTANDING THE FORMATION AND EVOLUTION OF PLANETARY SYSTEMS.
